The paper is about question answering over knowledge bases, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on knowledge bases and information retrieval also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of attention mechanisms and word interactions suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
